def get_stats(main_df, towns):
    # not sure if I need this
#     target_df.fillna('No data')
    
    for town in towns:
        target_df = main_df[main_df.CityMuniPSGC == town[1]]
        target_df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(target_df['DateRepConf'])
    #     if is_center:
    #         fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(40,6))
    #         target_df.groupby('date_converted')['CaseCode'].count().plot(ax=ax)
    #         print(target_df.groupby('Quarantined').size())
    #         print(target_df.groupby('Admitted').size())

        # Fill missing dates to 9 and get 7day rolling avg
        rolling = target_df.groupby('Date', as_index=False)['CaseCode'].count()
        rolling = rolling.set_index('Date')
        rolling.loc[pd.to_datetime('2020-03-15')] = [0]
        rolling = rolling.sort_index()
        rolling = rolling.resample('D').mean()
        rolling = rolling.fillna(0)
        rolling['svn_day_avg'] = rolling.iloc[:,0].rolling(window=7).mean()
        rolling = rolling.fillna(0)

        # Plot 7 day rolling avg
    #     fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(40,6))
    #     ax.title.set_text(f'{name} - 7 day moving average')
    #     rolling['svn_day_avg'].plot(ax=ax)
        yield (town[0], rolling, town[2])
In [7]:
def show_graph(nearby):
    town_name = []
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(40,10))
    for towndata in get_stats(raw_df, nearby):
        if towndata[2]:
            color = 'steelblue'
        else:
            color = 'coral'
        x = towndata[1].index.tolist()
        y = towndata[1].svn_day_avg.tolist()
        ax.plot(x, y, label = towndata[0], linestyle="solid", color=color)
        z = np.polyfit(range(len(x)), y, 1)
        p = np.poly1d(z)
        ax.plot(x ,p(range(len(x))),"r--", color=color)
        town_name.append(towndata[0])
    ax.set_title('-'.join(town_name) + ' 7 Day rolling average', fontdict={'fontsize': 10, 'fontweight': 'medium'})
    plt.legend()
    plt.show()
